FBIS3-4947 "dreas042_i_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-042 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Mar 1994 Cambodia General Says KRAF Still Controls Anlung Veng BK0203144394 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network in Cambodian 1300 GMT 2 Mar 94 BK0203144394 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network in Cambodian 1300 GMT 2 Mar 94 Language: Cambodian Article Type:BFN [Text] On the morning of 2 March, Brigadier General [name indistinct] informed reporters that the Anlung Veng area bordering Thailand in northern Cambodia -- which government forces captured from the Khmer Rouge on [words indistinct] -- was still under the control of government troops. This was a clarification of news reports that the Anlung Veng area had been retaken by the Khmer Rouge. Brig. Gen. [name indistinct] pointed out that in an effort to expand their territory, Khmer Royal Armed Forces [KRAF] troops were currently clearing mines laid around the area by the Khmer Rouge. The Khmer Rouge regrouped its troops in a bid to harass [words indistinct], where they cut down logs to sell to Thai merchants when they still controlled the area. The general said: Our helicopters [words indistinct] to bring supplies to KRAF troops in the Anlung Veng area and help to defend the area as well. It is worth recalling that Anlung Veng is the Khmer Rouge's major stronghold, built in 1979.
